---
name: integration-test-cycle
description: Develop tests for Nightscout API
version: 1.0.0
---

# Integration Test Cycle
# Docs: docs/backlogs/README.md (active work), docs/backlogs/*.md (details)
# Server: /home/bewest/src/worktrees/nightscout/cgm-pr-8447

MODEL claude-sonnet-4-20250514
ADAPTER copilot
MODE development
CONTEXT-LIMIT 50%
ON-CONTEXT-LIMIT compact
COMPACT-PRESERVE selected-task build-errors test-failures

RUN-ON-ERROR continue
RUN-OUTPUT-LIMIT 5K
RUN-TIMEOUT 120s
ALLOW-SHELL true

# === Phase 0: Status ===
ELIDE
RUN git status -s && curl -s localhost:1337/api/v1/status.json | head -1 || echo "Server not running"
ELIDE

PROMPT Check status. See `docs/backlogs/README.md` for context.

# === Phase 1: Select Task ===
ELIDE
RUN grep -E "^## 🔴|📋 Ready" docs/backlogs/README.md | head -15
ELIDE

PROMPT Pick a ready task. Backlog docs have full specs.

# === Phase 2: Execute ===
PROMPT Execute task. Explore `externals/` and backlog docs as needed.

# === Phase 3: Verify ===
ELIDE
RUN cd /home/bewest/src/worktrees/nightscout/cgm-pr-8447 && npm test 2>&1 | tail -5
ELIDE

PROMPT Verify tests pass.

# === Phase 4: Commit ===
PROMPT Update backlog status, commit changes.

ELIDE
RUN git status -s
ELIDE

# === Done ===
PROMPT Summary: Task completed, next steps.
